{
  "doc_id": "28866",
  "text": "In summary, our data suggest that ␣-synuclein pathology is not caused by loss of function of ␣-synuclein, but by gain of toxic function. Since single ␣-synuclein KO mice do not show significant neuropathology [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and knock-out of all three synuclein genes causes significant pathology only in older mice [CITATION_3] GretenHarrison et al., 2010; [CITATION_4] , suppression of ␣-synuclein expression alone may not be pathogenic in humans. Therapies to reduce or abolish ␣-synuclein expression may thus be a worthwhile strategy to decrease or prevent ␣-synucleininduced pathology.",
